        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>Early Western World coins by denomination name [300204073], Early Western World coins [300194572], coins by origin [300037223], coins (money) [300037222], money by form [300264712], money (objects) [300037316], exchange media (objects) [300387350], Exchange Media (hierarchy name) [300037221], Visual and Verbal Communication (hierarchy name) [300264552], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ancient Near Eastern coins, especially from Judea, issued during the 1st and 2nd centuries CE; also silver or cupronickel decimal coins of Israel. For Persian coins of the 6th and 5th centuries BCE, use "sigloi"; for coins issued in Sidon and Tyre from the 4th century BCE, prefer "tetradrachms."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Monedas antiguas del medio oriente, especialmente de Judea, emitidas durante los siglo I y II d.C; también monedas decimales de Israel de plata o cuproniquel. Para monedas persas de los siglos VI y V a.C., use "siglos"; para monedas emitidas en Sidón y Tiro desde el siglo IV a.C., prefiera "tetradracma".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Munten uit het oude Nabije Oosten, met name uit Juda; uitgegeven in de 1e en de 2e eeuw n.C. Ook gebruikt voor munten van zilver of koper-nikkel in het Israëlische decimale stelsel. Gebruik 'siglos' voor Perzische munten uit de 6e en 5e eeuw v.C.. Gebruik liever 'tetradrachmen' voor munten uitgegeven in Sidon en Tyrus in de 4e eeuw v.C.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>特指猶太區的古近東硬幣，發行於西元一世紀至二世紀間；也指以色列的十進制的銀幣或白銅硬幣。西元前六世紀與西元前五世紀的波斯硬幣，則稱「西格勞斯」；自西元前四世紀發行於西頓（Sidon）與泰爾（Tyre）地區的硬幣，則為「四德拉克馬」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Altorientalische Münze, besonders aus Judäa, ausgestellt im 1. und 2. Jh. nach Chr; auch Silber- oder Kupfernickel Dezimalmünzen Israels. Für persische Münzen des 6. und 5. Jh. v. Chr. verwendet man "Siglos"; für Münzen in Sidon und Tire aus dem 4. Jahrhundert v. Chr., bevorzugt man den Begriff "Tetradrachme".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
